+Subject: [PATCH 1/2] feat(linux): add headless EGL rendering support for
+ embedded platform

-Add headless OpenGL rendering via EGL for Linux embedded platform:
-
-- Create egl_headless.zig module that dynamically loads libEGL and libgbm
-- Support multiple platforms: GBM (hardware GPU), surfaceless, default
-- Support multiple OpenGL versions: 4.3, 3.3, ES 3.2, 3.1, 3.0
-- Add must_draw_from_app_thread for Linux to handle threadlocal glad context
-- Initialize EGL context in surfaceInit for embedded Linux
-- Add ghostty_surface_read_pixels for video frame capture
-
-This enables headless GPU rendering on Linux servers without a display,
-using DRM render nodes (/dev/dri/renderD128) for hardware acceleration.
